1 A fe lony conviction shall be grounds for removal of a person from
2 the office of notary public.
3 C. All notary commissions shall run in the name and by the
4 authority of the State of Oklahoma, be signed by the Secretary of
5 State, and sealed with the Great Seal of the State of Oklahoma.
6 Commissions shall not be attested.
7 D. Any person filing an application for a new notary commission
8 shall pay Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00) to the Secretary of State
9 with the application. Any person filing an application for a
10 renewal of a notary commission shall pay Twenty Dollars ($20.00) to
11 the Secretary of State with the application. Any person requiring
12 "same day filing service" shall pay Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00) to
13 the Secretary of State in addition to the applicable filing fee.
14 These funds shall be deposited in the Revolving Fund created for the
15 Secretary of State pursuant to the provisions of Section 276.1 of
16 Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
17 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1.2 of Title 49, unless there is
19 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. An applicant for a new notary commission must pass an
21 examination administered by the Office of the Oklahoma Secretary of
22 State or an entity approved by the Secretary of State. The
23 examination must be based on the course of study described in
24 subsection B of this section.
