1 B. The Secretary of State or an entity approved by the
2 Secretary of State shall offer regularly a course of study to
3 applicants who do not hold a notary commission in this state. The
4 course must cover the laws, rules, procedures, and ethics relevant
5 to notarial acts.
6 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 13 of Title 49, unless there is
8 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 A. Except for the notarial acts performed for an established
10 business relationship during the ordinary course of business, a
11 notary public shall maintain a journal in which the notary public
12 records all notarial acts that the notary public performs. The
13 notary public shall retain the journal for ten (10) years after the
14 performance of the last notarial act recorded in the journal.
15 B. A journal may be created on a tangible medium or in an
16 electronic format. A notary public shall maintain only one journal
17 at a time to chronicle all notarial acts, whether those notarial
18 acts are performed regarding tangible or electronic records. If the
19 journal is maintained on a tangible medium, it must be a permanent,
20 bound register with numbered pages. If the journal is maintained in
21 an electronic format, it must be in a permanent, tamper-evident
22 electronic format complying with the rules of the Secretary of
23 State.
24
